				"string" : "### 2. Shortest Path to Self — Navigational Semantics\n\nIn a topic-oriented environment (like GT + DMX + FedWiki), every concept or topic is a node in a semantic graph.\nFinding the *shortest path to self* means discovering how a given topic connects back to *your own current point of view* — your “self node” or *observer position*.\n\nMiller Columns help here because they:\n\n* expose **ancestral and sibling relations** visually (so you see where you are in the hierarchy),\n* and, when extended with associative links (not just parent/child), allow you to **trace minimal paths** in the conceptual graph.\n\nImagine each column as:\n\n```\n[Context] → [Concept] → [Example] → [Application] → [Self]\n```\n\nYou can read the *shortest path to self* as the sequence of selections that closes the loop between what you’re viewing and what you already *know* or *care about*.\n"
