					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "### 3. Accordion + Miller Columns = Two Axes of Sensemaking\n\n| Axis       | Layout         | Function                        | Cognitive Gesture           |\n| ---------- | -------------- | ------------------------------- | --------------------------- |\n| Vertical   | Accordion      | Reveal depth within a topic     | Unfold meaning              |\n| Horizontal | Miller Columns | Navigate relations among topics | Reconnect to self / context |\n\nUsed together:\n\n* The **accordion** lets you see *why* something matters.\n* The **Miller Columns** show *where* it fits and how to get *back to you* (and the snippet you are currently working on.\n\nThe process of folding this journey like an accordion involves expanding the context until the place (self) that provides the answer is found. This process is then reversed when closing the 'accordion', so to speak. It's like playing the accordion.\n\nSo, the shortest path to self is found by:\n\n1. Expanding (accordion) until the content resonates.\n2. Sliding (columns) until the path reconnects to your known interests or goals.\n"
